 \log x=\log(\sqrt{x}\cdot\sqrt{x})=\log\sqrt{x}+\log\sqrt{x}=2\log\sqrt{x} 
 \log\sqrt{x}=\frac{1}{2}\log x. 
 \log(x^k)=k\log x 
\displaystyle\log_bx=a, b^a=x
\displaystyle\log_b(x^m)=c, x^m=b^c
\implies b^c=x^m=(b^a)^m\implies b^c=b^{am}
\displaystyle\iff b^{c-am}=1=b^0
b\ne\pm1,0
\displaystyle\implies c-am=0
