x = b^{\log x} \implies \sqrt{x} =  b^{\log \sqrt{x}}
 \Rightarrow x = b^{2\log \sqrt{x}} \\  \Rightarrow b^{\log x} = b^{2\log \sqrt{x}} \\  \Rightarrow \log(x) = 2\log(\sqrt{x}) \\ \Rightarrow \frac{1}{2} \log(x) = \log(\sqrt{x}) 
 \large\text{RHS} = b^{\log(\sqrt{x}) + \log(\sqrt{x})} =  b^{\log(\sqrt{x})} \times b^{\log(\sqrt{x})} = \sqrt{x} \times \sqrt{x} = x = \text{LHS}
